The open source software archiver [[7-Zip]] uses a proprietary plugin under the gratis and [[source-available]] (but non-[[Free Software|free]]) "unRAR license" for decompression of newer RAR files. [http://download.cnet.com/Free-RAR-Extract-Frog/3000-2250_4-10804840.html Free RAR Extract Frog] is a skinable freeware frontend for the Windows unrar DLL. The free software Linux archivers [[File Roller]], [[Ark (computing)|Ark]], and [[Xarchiver]] can use the non-free [[unrar]] program to decompress RAR files, if it is found in the system path.
